Yobe governor, Mai Mala Buni, has approved the appointment of Alhaji Abdullahi Gashua a.k.a. Opera as his Chief of Staff. In a statement by the spokesperson to the Secretary to Yobe State Government, Shuaibu Abdullahi, on Tuesday in Damaturu, the governor said the appointment is with immediate effect. He said until his appointment as the Chief of Staff, Abdullahi Gashua was the Director of Administration of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Headquarters in Abuja. His appointment came hours after former Chief of Staff, Mohammed Nur Alkali, was announced as the new Permanent Secretary Special Duties, Government House, Damaturu. Gaidam appoints new Chief of Staff SSGs, others emerge as govs make first appointments Why states are yet to  name commissioners Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin